npc/rina: You want to understand what the Collector is. I can tell you.
npc/rina: Before she was part of this system, she was a debt collector working for one of the gambling platform's loan arms.
npc/rina: The platform would extend credit to players who ran out of money. Small amounts at first. Then larger. The interest compounded daily.
npc/rina: She was the one who called. Who showed up. Who threatened families and employers until the debt was paid.
npc/rina: She was good at her job. Efficient. Methodical. She never asked whether the debt was fair — only whether it was owed.
npc/rina: When the platform migrated into this layer of the network, she came with it. Willingly, from what I understand.
npc/rina: She does not need a body anymore. She is the debt itself — a process that runs endlessly, searching for accounts marked as unpaid.
npc/rina: Everyone who ever borrowed from the platform and could not repay is in her registry.
npc/rina: She does not forget. She does not expire. And she is getting closer to this part of the network.
